name: CoronaryArteryDisease
title: Coronary Artery Disease
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining CAD diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad group of diagnosis concepts for coronary artery disease (CAD).),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the disorder branch, though some can be in the situation branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes coronary artery arteriosclerosis, stenosis, thrombosis, embolism, or occlusion. Includes acute and chronic ischemic heart disease and angina.  Also includes treatments of coronary disease such as coronary bypass surgery and coronary stenting, as well as history of myocardial infarction.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes silent coronary vasospastic disease, congenital coronary anomalies, and transient myocardial ischemia of newborns.)
